# CLAUDE.md

This file provides guidance to Claude Code (claude.ai/code) when working with code in this repository.

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev        # Start dev server (Vite + Electron hot reload)
npm run build      # TypeScript check + Vite build
npm run dist       # Build → package Windows installer
npm run dist:win   # Build → package Windows x64 installer + portable
```

No test suite exists in this project.

## Architecture

**Stack:** Electron + React 18 + TypeScript + Zustand + Tailwind CSS + Vite

### IPC boundary (Electron ↔ Renderer)

All communication between the renderer and the main process goes through the contextBridge:

- `electron/main.ts` — IPC handlers (`ipcMain.handle`) + Groq API calls
- `electron/preload.ts` — exposes `window.electronAPI` via `contextBridge`
- `src/types/electron.d.ts` — TypeScript types for `window.electronAPI`

The Groq API key is hardcoded as `GROQ_API_KEY` in `electron/main.ts`. It never crosses to the renderer.

### State management (Zustand stores)

- `useDisplayEditorStore` — the active `DisplayConfig` (elements, canvas size, bg color), selection state, grid settings. `loadConfig()` replaces the entire canvas state — used by both AI features.
- `useStyleStore` — app-wide UI theme (`colors` object with primary/surface/border/etc.). All components read `colors` from here instead of hardcoding values.
- `useRemoteStore` — remote controller button grid state (separate from display editor).

### Layout (`src/App.tsx`)

Three-panel flex layout: `ElementPanel (left 240px) | DisplayEditor (flex-1) | TextGenerator (right 300px, toggleable)`. Modals (`ImageAnalyzer`, `ExportModal`) render as fixed overlays on top.

### Display element types

`DisplayElement` has 6 types: `indicator` (LED/status), `gauge` (progress bar), `numeric` (value readout), `label`, `title`, `logo`. Canvas default size is 480×320.

### AI features

- **바이브 코딩 (TextGenerator)** — right side panel, toggled by header button. Sends a text prompt to `generate-layout` IPC → Groq `llama-4-scout` → returns `DisplayConfig` JSON → user selects elements → `loadConfig()`.
- **AI 분석 (ImageAnalyzer)** — modal overlay. Sends base64 image to `analyze-image` IPC → Groq vision → same flow.

Both features use `meta-llama/llama-4-scout-17b-16e-instruct` via `https://api.groq.com/openai/v1/chat/completions`.

### Export

`src/utils/exporter.ts` generates a self-contained HTML file (no dependencies) for the remote controller panel. The display editor export is handled in `src/components/export/ExportModal.tsx`.
